-- UPS reports loss on pension charge
-- 
-- Wed Jan 30, 2008 9:06am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/30/us-ups-results-idUSWNAS842120080130

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Package delivery company United Parcel Service Inc ( UPS.N ) on Wednesday reported a quarterly loss, citing a $6.1 billion charge related to transferring employees from a multi-employer pension fund. 

 The Atlanta-based company reported a fourth-quarter net loss of $2.58 billion, or $2.46 a share, compared with a net profit of $1.13 billion, or $1.04 a share, a year earlier. Excluding the one-time charge, UPS earned $1.13 per share. (Reporting by  Nick Carey , editing by John Wallace)